         <abstract id="aspace_994c489baf951bb1afc65424854fc196">Professional papers of opthalmologist Arthur Meyer Yudkin, 1917-1942. Includes correspondence with physicians, professors, patients, and other individuals, as well as papers relating to Yudkin's "Lemon Juice Discovery," in which he offered vitamins as a therapeutic measure for the treatment and prevention of ocular diseases.

Correspondents include Percy H. Fridenberg (1868-1960), Joseph Igersheimer (1879-1965), Lafayette B. Mendel (1872-1935), Mark J. Schoenberg (1874-1945), and William C. Stadie (1886-1959), as well as the American Academy of Ophthalmology, Connecticut Board of Education for the Blind, Connecticut School for the Blind (now Oak Hill School), and National Society for the Prevention of Blindness.</abstract>
